  "prompt": "How would you know that a guy has a crush on you or likes you even though if you are friends?",
  "response": "It can be tricky to tell if a friend has a crush on you, but here are some signs to look for:\n\n**Body Language & Nonverbal Cues:**\n\n*   **Prolonged eye contact:** He holds your gaze a little longer than usual, or smiles when you make eye contact.\n*   **Mirroring:** He unconsciously mirrors your body language, like crossing his legs when you do, or leaning in when you lean in.\n*   **Proximity:** He finds excuses to be near you, always sitting next to you, or lingering in your space.\n*   **Physical touch:** Increased, seemingly innocent touch. This could be a playful nudge, a light touch on your arm, or finding excuses to brush against you. Pay attention to the context and frequency.\n*   **Blushing or fidgeting:** He gets flustered, blushes, or fidgets when talking to you, especially if he's normally calm and collected.\n*   **Open posture:** He turns his body towards you when you're talking, even in a group. His body language indicates he's engaged and interested in you.\n\n**Verbal Clues & Behavior:**\n\n*   **He's extra attentive:** He remembers small details about you, your interests, and things you've told him. He asks thoughtful questions and actively listens.\n*   **He teases you playfully:** Lighthearted teasing can be a way to gauge your reaction and flirt.\n*   **He compliments you frequently:** He goes beyond generic compliments and notices specific things about you, your personality, or your accomplishments.\n*   **He makes an effort to spend one-on-one time with you:** He suggests activities just the two of you can do, outside of your usual group activities.\n*   **He's always available to help you:** He goes out of his way to assist you with tasks, offer support, or be there when you need him.\n*   **He gets jealous or possessive:** If you talk about other guys, he might seem subtly jealous or change the subject.\n*   **He laughs at your jokes (even the bad ones):** He finds you funny, even when you're not trying to be.\n*   **He talks about the future with you:** He might casually mention things you could do together in the future.\n*   **He opens up about his feelings:** He shares personal information and vulnerabilities with you, indicating he trusts you and wants to connect on a deeper level.\n*   **His friends act differently around you:** If his friends know about his crush, they might tease him, wink at you, or act differently when you're around.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Context is key:** Consider the context of the situation. Some of these signs might just be part of his personality or the nature of your friendship.\n*   **Observe patterns:** Don't rely on just one instance. Look for a pattern of behaviors over time.\n*   **Trust your gut:** Sometimes you just have a feeling. If you suspect he likes you, trust your intuition.\n*   **Don't overthink it:** Try not to analyze every little thing. Let the relationship unfold naturally.\n\n**What To Do If You Suspect He Likes You:**\n\n*   **Observe and gather more evidence:** Before making any assumptions, continue to observe his behavior.\n*   **Reflect on your own feelings:** Do you reciprocate his feelings? Are you comfortable with the possibility of taking your friendship to the next level?\n*   **Have an open and honest conversation (if appropriate):** If you feel comfortable, you could subtly test the waters by talking about dating or relationships. Or, if you're sure of your feelings and his, you could have a direct conversation about it.\n*   **Respect his feelings (regardless of your decision):** Whether you reciprocate his feelings or not, be kind and respectful of his emotions.\n\nUltimately, the best way to know for sure is to communicate openly and honestly. However, by paying attention to these signs, you can get a better idea of whether your friend might have a crush on you. Good luck!\n",
